The paper deals with the problem of lossy source coding, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. The paper specifically focuses on the three-node multiterminal lossy source coding problem, which is a subfield of information theory and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses several relevant source coding settings, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper uses mathematical techniques to derive an inner bound, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
